{
  "info": {
    "name": "Module 4 — Google Calendar CRUD (JWT Bearer)",
    "description": "Project Session A verification: full create/read/update/delete on Google Calendar events.\n\nGETTING THE TOKEN: Postman can't sign JWTs into the 'assertion' parameter, so mint the token with the 6-line Anonymous Apex block in resources/phase-3-jwt-bearer/apex/anonymous-scripts.apex (Session A block), copy the debugged TOKEN value into the collection variable google_access_token. Tokens live ~1 hour — mint a fresh one when calls start returning 401. That re-signing IS the JWT bearer flow's 'refresh'.\n\nVariables to set:\n- google_access_token: from the Apex debug log\n- calendar_id: from Google Calendar > Settings and sharing > Integrate calendar (your Gmail address for the primary calendar). The calendar must be shared with the service account with 'Make changes to events'.\n\nKeep calendar.google.com open while running — events appear, rename, and vanish live.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "google_access_token", "value": "PASTE_TOKEN_FROM_APEX_DEBUG", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "calendar_id", "value": "you@gmail.com", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "event_id", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. CREATE event (POST)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
              "    const ev = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('event_id', ev.id);",
              "    console.log('Event id saved: ' + ev.id + ' — open it: ' + ev.htmlLink);",
              "}",
              "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{google_access_token}}", "type": "text" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"summary\": \"Kickoff — created from Postman\",\n  \"start\": { \"dateTime\": \"2026-07-15T10:00:00Z\" },\n  \"end\":   { \"dateTime\": \"2026-07-15T10:30:00Z\" }\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{calendar_id}}/events",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": ["www", "googleapis", "com"],
          "path": ["calendar", "v3", "calendars", "{{calendar_id}}", "events"]
        },
        "description": "Datetimes must be RFC 3339 (e.g. 2026-07-15T10:00:00Z). The response includes id (auto-saved) and htmlLink — a direct URL to the event. 404 here usually means the calendar isn't shared with the service account (Google hides unshared calendars as 404, not 403)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "2. READ event (GET)",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{google_access_token}}", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{calendar_id}}/events/{{event_id}}",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": ["www", "googleapis", "com"],
          "path": ["calendar", "v3", "calendars", "{{calendar_id}}", "events", "{{event_id}}"]
        },
        "description": "Reads the event created in request 1 (its id was auto-saved)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "3. UPDATE event (PATCH)",
      "request": {
        "method": "PATCH",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{google_access_token}}", "type": "text" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"summary\": \"Kickoff — RESCHEDULED from Postman\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{calendar_id}}/events/{{event_id}}",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": ["www", "googleapis", "com"],
          "path": ["calendar", "v3", "calendars", "{{calendar_id}}", "events", "{{event_id}}"]
        },
        "description": "PATCH = partial update: only the fields you send change (Google's events reference documents patch semantics). Watch the title change live in the calendar."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4. DELETE event (DELETE)",
      "request": {
        "method": "DELETE",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{google_access_token}}", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{calendar_id}}/events/{{event_id}}",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": ["www", "googleapis", "com"],
          "path": ["calendar", "v3", "calendars", "{{calendar_id}}", "events", "{{event_id}}"]
        },
        "description": "Expect 204 No Content. Run it twice on purpose: the second answers 410 Gone — 'already deleted' is a state to expect, not a bug (Module 2's 404 lesson, Google flavor)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "5. LIST upcoming events (GET)",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{google_access_token}}", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{calendar_id}}/events?maxResults=5&orderBy=startTime&singleEvents=true",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": ["www", "googleapis", "com"],
          "path": ["calendar", "v3", "calendars", "{{calendar_id}}", "events"],
          "query": [
            { "key": "maxResults", "value": "5" },
            { "key": "orderBy", "value": "startTime" },
            { "key": "singleEvents", "value": "true" }
          ]
        },
        "description": "Bonus: the list endpoint — useful for the homework and for verifying what the service account can actually see."
      }
    }
  ]
}
